Fed Sells $1.37 Billion of Debt Under Operation Twist

-- B y   L i z   M c C o r m i c k
-- 
2011-10-17T15:05:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/fed-sells-1-37-billion-of-debt-under-operation-twist.html
The  Federal Reserve  sold $1.37
billion in Treasury Inflation Protected Securities as part of
its plan to lower borrowing costs that’s become known as
Operation Twist.  The central bank sold debt maturing from July 2013 to July
2014, according to the Federal Reserve Bank of  New York ’s
 website .  The Fed is replacing $400 billion of short-term debt in its
portfolio with longer-term Treasuries in an effort to reduce
borrowing costs further and counter rising risks of a recession.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Liz McCormick in New York at 
 emccormick7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dave Liedtka at 
 dliedtka@bloomberg.net  